=Episode 3=

3
00:00:10,420 --> 00:00:12,740
(Chen Residence)

4
00:00:21,140 --> 00:00:22,060
(Not bad.)

5
00:00:22,610 --> 00:00:24,650
(This is exactly like the Chen
Theater Troupe that I drew.)

6
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:35,290
Interesting.

7
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,300
You?

8
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:47,300
You

9
00:00:47,980 --> 00:00:48,500
know me?

10
00:00:48,890 --> 00:00:50,660
(He was always there eating dumplings.)

11
00:00:51,010 --> 00:00:52,260
(Why did he come here this time?)

12
00:00:53,260 --> 00:00:54,330
Why are you here?

13
00:00:54,940 --> 00:00:56,300
I'm Song Keyang, a wandering musician.

14
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:57,690
I heard the Chen Theater Troupe
is recruiting a musician

15
00:00:57,820 --> 00:00:58,100
so I came.

16
00:00:58,260 --> 00:00:58,570
(What's going on?)

17
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:00,570
(Why is it going off-script today?)

18
00:01:01,210 --> 00:01:02,730
(It's different
from the previous cycles.)

19
00:01:04,570 --> 00:01:05,300
My master and my seniors

20
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:05,980
went out.

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:06,890
I don't have time to entertain you.

22
00:01:07,210 --> 00:01:07,850
Come...

23
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:10,170
Come again tomorrow.

24
00:01:10,850 --> 00:01:11,260
But I...

25
00:01:12,330 --> 00:01:13,370
I have traveled for many days.

26
00:01:13,730 --> 00:01:15,100
If I can't meet Troupe Leader Chen,

27
00:01:15,250 --> 00:01:16,100
I won't let you leave.

28
00:01:16,650 --> 00:01:18,100
Why are you doing this?

29
00:01:18,180 --> 00:01:19,010
Like I said,

30
00:01:19,010 --> 00:01:19,780
I'm busy today.

31
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:21,010
Come again tomorrow.

32
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:22,970
Will you move aside?

33
00:01:23,050 --> 00:01:23,250
No.

34
00:01:24,780 --> 00:01:25,500
Bugger off.

35
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:29,250
Liu Xiaoxiao.

36
00:01:29,730 --> 00:01:30,580
You are barbaric.

37
00:01:31,010 --> 00:01:32,220
Wait!

38
00:01:42,010 --> 00:01:42,690
(Master.)

39
00:01:43,330 --> 00:01:44,010
(Seniors.)

40
00:01:44,290 --> 00:01:45,460
(I will not give up.)

41
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:47,690
Liu Xiaoxiao.

42
00:01:53,140 --> 00:01:54,610
(Is it because I'm on writer's block)

43
00:01:54,690 --> 00:01:55,460
(that Liu Xiaoxiao)

44
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:56,370
(is stuck on this day forever?)

45
00:01:59,650 --> 00:02:02,500
The sky is starry
but the moon is gloomy.

46
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:05,780
The world is full of lives
but justice does not prevail.

47
00:02:06,610 --> 00:02:09,010
In the mortal martial arts world,

48
00:02:09,970 --> 00:02:11,650
the vainglorious pursuit

49
00:02:12,010 --> 00:02:13,420
is but a dream.

50
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:18,420
(I'll steal the puppets)

51
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:19,420
(and now, you cannot perform.)

52
00:02:22,660 --> 00:02:23,610
No matter what,

53
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,580
I will save all of you.

54
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:30,450
It's you.

55
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:31,940
You know me?

56
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:33,580
No.

57
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:35,020
But I can read someone's fortune.

58
00:02:37,330 --> 00:02:38,580
Let me see.

59
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:39,780
You just had dumplings

60
00:02:40,330 --> 00:02:41,170
and you're here

61
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:42,860
because you want to join
the Chen Theater Troupe.

62
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:44,940
You're good.

63
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:46,420
Do we have a guest?

64
00:02:49,140 --> 00:02:49,810
Do me a favor.

65
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:53,660
Hi, Troupe Leader Chen.

66
00:02:56,380 --> 00:02:57,020
You are...

67
00:02:57,140 --> 00:02:59,300
- He's a musician who wants to join us.
- I...

68
00:03:00,690 --> 00:03:01,090
Precisely.

69
00:03:01,170 --> 00:03:02,580
You're the rare talent

70
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:03,970
the shopkeeper mentioned?

71
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,140
She said your techniques

72
00:03:05,140 --> 00:03:06,140
could move the sky.

73
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:06,940
She flatters me.

74
00:03:06,970 --> 00:03:08,050
So young and full of potential.

75
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:10,380
Why don't you perform

76
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:11,020
before me?

77
00:03:11,050 --> 00:03:11,810
Sure.

78
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:13,140
Oh, Master.

79
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:14,250
Make sure you evaluate his techniques

80
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:15,250
thoroughly.

81
00:03:15,610 --> 00:03:15,810
I

82
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:17,860
will leave you all be.

83
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:18,810
But...

84
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:20,020
Stay right there.

85
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,250
What's behind you?

86
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:23,220
(Oh, no.)

87
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,740
(I can't let him find out right now.)

88
00:03:25,020 --> 00:03:26,660
(Otherwise, the performance
will go on as usual.)

89
00:03:26,690 --> 00:03:27,250
I...

90
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:29,170
I was performing a puppet show with him.

91
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:33,740
What did you two perform?

92
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:36,890
Master.

93
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,940
Don't you want
to evaluate his techniques?

94
00:03:39,050 --> 00:03:39,380
Should we

95
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:41,050
perform before you?

96
00:03:41,530 --> 00:03:42,420
Great idea.

97
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:43,090
Go ahead.

98
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:45,860
That's odd.

99
00:03:46,170 --> 00:03:47,580
She retains her memory then?

100
00:03:47,970 --> 00:03:49,450
Help me.

101
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:12,060
(Marionette is an important form of
theater performance in Ancient China.)

102
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:12,940
Not bad.

103
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:14,090
You have improved.

104
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,170
Your fundamentals are more solid
than before.

105
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:17,610
I can tell you didn't skip
your training.

106
00:04:20,050 --> 00:04:21,610
(Master, seniors!)

107
00:04:25,970 --> 00:04:26,690
Master.

108
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:29,580
I will train hard.

109
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:32,490
You won't abandon me, will you?

110
00:04:33,530 --> 00:04:34,530
My sweet child.

111
00:04:34,810 --> 00:04:35,460
What are you on about?

112
00:04:36,180 --> 00:04:36,970
I won't abandon you.

113
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:38,420
Master.

114
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:41,930
Musician Zhang hurt his hands
during rehearsal.

115
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:43,060
He won't be able to perform today.

116
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:49,420
I may not be talented

117
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:50,370
but I'm good at improvising.

118
00:04:50,650 --> 00:04:51,210
Perhaps

119
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:52,090
I can give it a go?

120
00:04:53,090 --> 00:04:53,650
(That might work.)

121
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:55,370
He's a new musician

122
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:56,300
but he plays very well.

123
00:04:56,580 --> 00:04:57,620
In this case,

124
00:04:58,250 --> 00:05:00,140
you shall take Musician Zhang's spot.

125
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:04,460
(Musician's bracelet)

126
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,210
This doesn't work.

127
00:05:06,490 --> 00:05:07,810
That doesn't work as well.

128
00:05:10,690 --> 00:05:12,180
What the heck?

129
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:13,530
Why can't anything

130
00:05:13,530 --> 00:05:14,300
work for once?

131
00:05:15,460 --> 00:05:16,810
(Pretend to be kidnapped)
This doesn't work too.

132
00:05:16,970 --> 00:05:17,740
Neither does this

133
00:05:17,810 --> 00:05:18,770
nor this.

134
00:05:19,740 --> 00:05:20,460
What are you doing here?

135
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:22,420
Song Keyang, you...

136
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:28,020
You...

137
00:05:28,690 --> 00:05:30,020
Are so handsome.

138
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:30,420
What are you doing?

139
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:32,620
(How can she be that open-minded?)

140
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:33,810
(No, I can't do that.)

141
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:35,620
Let go of me.

142
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:36,580
You...

143
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:37,720
I...

144
00:05:38,210 --> 00:05:39,210
Youhai!

145
00:05:39,490 --> 00:05:40,180
That's him.

146
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:42,490
He joined the troupe

147
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:44,770
to make a pass at me.

148
00:05:45,210 --> 00:05:45,490
I...

149
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,250
You look like a fine gentleman

150
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:48,490
but you took advantage of Xiaoxiao.

151
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:49,930
Let go of me now.

152
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:51,210
Open your eyes and see.

153
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:52,810
She made a pass at me.

154
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:53,740
You touched her first.

155
00:05:54,090 --> 00:05:54,770
Leave now.

156
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,090
Or I'll have someone

157
00:05:56,180 --> 00:05:56,930
beat you to a pulp!

158
00:05:57,580 --> 00:05:58,180
Fine.

159
00:05:58,620 --> 00:05:59,300
I can't be bothered.

160
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:05,770
Liu Xiaoxiao.

161
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:07,140
I don't care
what you're trying to achieve

162
00:06:07,650 --> 00:06:08,340
but you'll beg me one day.

163
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:11,580
(What does he mean?)

164
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:13,370
(Is there something)

165
00:06:13,370 --> 00:06:14,140
(I should know?)

166
