♪The dusk outside the window
is spreading♪

167
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:21,520
♪The lanterns light up
with anticipation♪

168
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:26,670
♪The sea of lights illuminates
the entire theater♪

169
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,600
♪The galaxy sprawls across the sky♪

170
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:34,440
♪The moon shows itself♪

171
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:39,760
♪Gazing at the myriad lives♪

172
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:43,560
♪The bell chimes and the lady dances♪

173
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:47,190
♪Her movements are mysterious
and graceful♪

174
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:52,430
♪A woman can solicit cheers
and applause too♪

175
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:56,390
♪Chatters fill the well-lit hall♪

176
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:59,830
♪Holding a red candle by the stage♪

177
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:05,120
♪Witnessing the blooming and wilting,
oh, the freedom♪

178
